Mari Gas Discovers Crude Oil Reserves in Pakistan’s Karak Block

-- B y   K h u r r u m   A n i s
-- 
2011-10-14T06:19:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/mari-gas-discovers-crude-oil-reserves-in-pakistan-s-karak-block.html
Mari Gas Co., a Pakistani energy
exploration company, discovered crude oil in Karak block on the
border of the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa and Punjab provinces.  The oil was found at a depth of 5,350 meters (17,555 feet)
in the Halini well, the company said in a filing to the  stock
exchange  today. Tests indicated output of 1,700 barrels a day,
it said.  Mari Gas is partially owned by Mol  Pakistan  Oil & Gas BV, a
unit of Mol Nyrt.,  Hungary ’s largest refiner. Mol Pakistan has a
40 percent share in the Karak block, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Khurrum Anis in Karachi at 
